snippet.textDisplay: my dad's a doctor and over 50, I'm so scared for him and my mom. He's had the weekend off and showed me the list of patients in the icu and all but 4 were respiratory illnesses with some on ventilators. The testing for Covid19 went from 2 days to 5-8 days to get the results back. I remember telling him how Corona was going to be worse than SARS back in January and he didn't believe me until the self quarantine came into effect. The next day as Chief of Surgery he canceled all elected surgeries for the hospital till further notice and got a huge backlash from the administration. 2 weeks later and the cdc calls for that exact measure everyone had previously called too extreme. He definitely saved lives doing that I hope everyone realizes the severity and are proactive in limiting the spread. God bless us
